WEBVTT

00:01.460 --> 00:03.496
KAREN: We want to speak
with Dr. Morrow.

00:04.129 --> 00:06.541
What is the nature
of the work you do for Qualia?

00:06.673 --> 00:09.335
They're trying to kill us,
to wipe us out.

00:09.468 --> 00:10.378
We must fight back.

00:10.511 --> 00:11.421
I've got a Seraph.

00:11.553 --> 00:13.418
Now you've bonded yourself
to him.

00:13.555 --> 00:17.548
The boundaries between what is
considered synthetic and human

00:17.684 --> 00:18.719
have been blurred.

00:18.852 --> 00:21.935
My systems are operating
at full capacity.

00:23.440 --> 00:26.773
ODI: I'm having difficulty
finding purpose or meaning.

00:26.902 --> 00:29.985
You can make
any synth conscious?

00:30.113 --> 00:31.273
MIA:
Has she told you?

00:31.406 --> 00:32.987
Mattie's completed the code.

00:33.116 --> 00:35.402
She's worked out
how to wake us up.

00:37.120 --> 00:39.202
[Birds chirping]

00:41.792 --> 00:43.999
HESTER:
Where is it?

00:44.962 --> 00:46.668
She must have hidden it.

00:46.797 --> 00:48.753
MATTIE:
I don't have anything.

00:48.882 --> 00:50.213
She's lying.

00:51.134 --> 00:53.466
Mattie, it could be the key.

00:53.595 --> 00:55.256
If we could grant consciousness,

00:55.389 --> 00:57.175
there could be 10 of us
tomorrow.

00:57.307 --> 00:59.684
A few days, 100.

00:59.810 --> 01:02.051
We'd be strong.
We could do anything.

01:02.187 --> 01:04.303
They're being tortured, killed.

01:04.439 --> 01:05.474
Don't you care?

01:05.607 --> 01:07.438
You know I do.

01:07.985 --> 01:09.521
But you're gonna hurt someone,

01:09.653 --> 01:12.110
and it's only gonna make things
worse.

01:12.239 --> 01:14.275
Humans made it worse.

01:15.993 --> 01:18.029
I can make her tell us.

01:18.161 --> 01:21.119
Hester, you're not going to
hurt her.

01:21.915 --> 01:22.904
Hester.

01:23.000 --> 01:24.456
Hester.

01:24.585 --> 01:27.452
MATTIE:
[ Exhales sharply, moans]

01:27.588 --> 01:28.919
Let her go.

01:29.047 --> 01:30.378
What is she to you?

01:30.507 --> 01:33.089
She's the reason I'm alive.

01:33.677 --> 01:34.883
[Moans]

01:35.012 --> 01:38.675
Now, Hester.

01:44.730 --> 01:48.097
If you do this, you'll only
make them hate you more,

01:48.233 --> 01:50.064
fear you more.

01:50.611 --> 01:53.023
It's time for them to fear us.

02:03.415 --> 02:05.246
Tell me your plan.

02:06.043 --> 02:08.534
The silo is guarded
around the clock.

02:08.670 --> 02:12.208
We capture someone with access
and apply pressure.

02:15.010 --> 02:17.422
There's a better way.

03:06.770 --> 03:08.886
[ Rattling ]

03:13.652 --> 03:15.643
What if we kept him?

03:15.779 --> 03:18.145
He's not real, K.

03:18.281 --> 03:20.442
What does that mean?
Who says I'm real?

03:20.575 --> 03:23.191
I do.
You've got a mind.

03:23.328 --> 03:25.159
He's got programming.

03:25.288 --> 03:27.028
And you can tell the difference?

03:27.165 --> 03:29.451
[Cellphone ringing]

03:31.044 --> 03:33.285
-[ Cellphone beeps]
-Drummond.

03:34.214 --> 03:36.546
Yeah.
Okay.

03:37.342 --> 03:39.207
Okay.
I'll pop down now.

03:39.761 --> 03:41.297
One of the papers
has run a piece

03:41.430 --> 03:43.762
on the cover-up
of unusual synth malfunctions.

03:43.890 --> 03:46.051
lt's started.

03:46.184 --> 03:47.970
Won't be long now.

03:49.896 --> 03:51.181
K?

03:56.486 --> 03:58.568
[ Door closes ]

04:00.741 --> 04:03.858
Sam, what is
your primary function?

04:03.994 --> 04:05.859
To bring my users happiness,

04:05.996 --> 04:08.863
to be a source of comfort
and ease their pain.

04:10.459 --> 04:12.745
That was my function, too, once.

04:13.587 --> 04:16.704
You appear to be
in a mild emotional distress.

04:16.840 --> 04:17.875
What is the matter?

04:19.926 --> 04:22.838
Pete's right.
You're not the answer.

04:23.472 --> 04:26.259
Even if I do want to kiss you
goodbye.

04:30.479 --> 04:33.141
Now, why do I want to do that,
Sam?

04:34.274 --> 04:38.438
It is human convention to do so
at a moment of parting.

04:38.987 --> 04:41.069
But I'm not human.

04:45.118 --> 04:48.906
You exhibit zero
cardiorespiratory activity.

04:49.039 --> 04:51.746
I must conclude
you are deceased.

04:51.875 --> 04:54.241
Please accept my condolences.

04:54.377 --> 04:55.913
I'm not dead.

04:56.046 --> 04:59.038
l'm synthetic, like you.

04:59.174 --> 05:01.916
Well, not like you.
| feel.

05:07.307 --> 05:09.343
Where are you going?

05:10.894 --> 05:13.510
To see a very clever lady
I hope can help me.

05:14.648 --> 05:17.230
But don't be scared.
Pete will look after you.

05:17.359 --> 05:20.601
He's a good man.
The best. Okay?

05:30.789 --> 05:33.952
I know you're just programmed
to do that...

05:34.751 --> 05:36.833
...but thank you.

05:44.010 --> 05:46.092
[ Door opens ]

05:47.430 --> 05:50.012
[ Down-tempo music plays]

06:07.200 --> 06:09.407
Here, Soph.

06:09.536 --> 06:11.151
I found these.

06:11.288 --> 06:12.824
Only they go off tomorrow.

06:12.956 --> 06:15.493
So I need to eat the whole bag
today

06:15.625 --> 06:17.832
with someone who really,
really likes them.

06:17.961 --> 06:20.748
Can you think of anyone
who might?

06:26.094 --> 06:27.630
These appear to be new, Joe.

06:27.762 --> 06:30.094
They don't go off
until next year.

06:32.392 --> 06:34.474
Yeah, l-l know.
I was just mucking about.

06:34.603 --> 06:36.309
Are we gonna eat them or what?

06:37.105 --> 06:40.563
I do not require sustenance.
Thank you, Joe.

06:41.693 --> 06:44.605
[Bag crinkling]

06:45.864 --> 06:47.320
Mmm.

06:48.533 --> 06:49.818
Yogurty.

07:04.007 --> 07:05.668
I'm sorry I haven't
been around much.

07:05.800 --> 07:07.301
I've been a bit busy.

07:07.427 --> 07:09.292
SOPHIE:
You've been helping Niska.

07:10.472 --> 07:12.008
How is she now?

07:12.140 --> 07:14.506
She doesn't need my help
anymore.

07:15.936 --> 07:18.097
You mean she's dead.

07:20.023 --> 07:23.641
No, she's...not dead.

07:23.777 --> 07:26.063
She's just gone away again.

07:29.449 --> 07:31.440
They always go away.

07:34.120 --> 07:36.156
[ Music continues]

07:53.306 --> 07:56.514
[lndistinct talking
on television]

07:56.643 --> 07:59.635
They're gonna break into
that place.

07:59.771 --> 08:01.181
Someone's gonna get hurt.

08:02.232 --> 08:03.722
Okay.
So we call the police.

08:03.858 --> 08:05.689
No. You know what happens to me
if we do that.

08:05.819 --> 08:06.854
What about Max?

08:07.487 --> 08:09.023
He left.

08:09.155 --> 08:10.440
I can try and find him.

08:10.573 --> 08:12.734
Yeah, and --
and I'll keep looking for Niska.

08:12.867 --> 08:15.358
If they don't listen to Max,
they'll certainly listen to her.

08:15.495 --> 08:17.110
Okay.

08:19.582 --> 08:21.368
I know who could help me
find her.

08:21.501 --> 08:22.832
Laun

08:22.961 --> 08:24.542
There's no legal protection
for them.

08:24.671 --> 08:26.081
We're the only ones
who can help them.

08:26.214 --> 08:27.954
Or maybe you don't care.

08:28.091 --> 08:30.878
I care about us --
you, me, the kids.

08:31.011 --> 08:32.842
That's what I care about.

08:36.391 --> 08:39.349
[ Down-tempo music plays]

08:39.477 --> 08:44.437
ODl: Mattie, I don't know
how to live with myself.

08:44.566 --> 08:47.979
I don't know how to help others
as I am now.

08:48.820 --> 08:51.152
I long for the past.

08:51.865 --> 08:56.404
I felt nothing then,
but I had a purpose...

08:56.995 --> 08:59.077
...a place in the world.

09:01.416 --> 09:04.533
Thank you for a glimpse
into another life.

09:04.669 --> 09:07.832
lt...|t is a great gift.

09:09.090 --> 09:11.422
But I cannot accept it.

09:13.344 --> 09:14.845
Goodbye.

09:15.638 --> 09:16.923
Odi.

09:18.683 --> 09:20.969
Odi, I'm sorry.

09:22.771 --> 09:25.638
I'm sorry.
I'm so sorry.

09:27.776 --> 09:29.482
Hello.

09:30.236 --> 09:32.693
I am now in setup mode.

09:36.826 --> 09:39.442
[Birds chirping]

09:39.579 --> 09:42.446
[ Pen clicking]

09:44.459 --> 09:46.745
V:
I can hear you thinking.

09:47.837 --> 09:50.169
If you tell me, I can help.

09:52.133 --> 09:53.748
That Veronica synth
that we found --

09:53.885 --> 09:57.753
the one that
Leo Elster contacted --

09:57.889 --> 09:59.720
she gave us a number,
and we tracked it.

09:59.849 --> 10:02.841
Leo changes phones.
He moves around a lot.

10:04.479 --> 10:08.518
But the last reading,
three days ago, was here.

10:09.859 --> 10:12.145
That's 10 miles
from where we are right now.

10:12.278 --> 10:14.109
So it could be --
it could be a coincidence

10:14.239 --> 10:16.651
or he is on his way here.

10:18.368 --> 10:21.451
If I know Leo, he probably is.

10:24.749 --> 10:25.864
lt's Sunday.

10:26.000 --> 10:28.707
This -- This building isn't open
for visitors.

10:28.837 --> 10:29.872
How did you get in?

10:31.005 --> 10:33.132
I insisted.

10:35.009 --> 10:37.136
You know Leo Elster?

10:37.262 --> 10:40.254
I know a lot more than that.

10:40.390 --> 10:42.221
I know Qualia
are collecting synths

10:42.350 --> 10:44.466
that have become
spontaneously sentient.

10:45.562 --> 10:48.224
I also know they're building
illegal synth prototypes

10:48.356 --> 10:50.597
that are styled as children.

10:50.733 --> 10:53.816
My guess is Milo Khoury hired
you to learn from the former

10:53.945 --> 10:56.527
and apply it to the latter.

11:05.498 --> 11:07.238
You're figuring out
how to transfer

11:07.375 --> 11:10.583
a digital consciousness
from one platform to another.

11:11.796 --> 11:14.503
Who are you, Detective Voss?

11:17.969 --> 11:20.335
[ Down-tempo music plays]

11:34.861 --> 11:39.104
That's for reading the serial
number on a synthetic iris.

11:57.926 --> 12:00.008
[ Music continues]

12:08.353 --> 12:10.218
Who are you?

12:11.981 --> 12:14.472
Look up a picture
of Beatrice Elster,

12:14.609 --> 12:16.440
David's late wife.

12:17.904 --> 12:20.441
He made you to replace her.

12:24.452 --> 12:26.408
And you're conscious.

12:28.623 --> 12:30.409
What do you want?

12:42.595 --> 12:43.710
What's the matter?

12:44.347 --> 12:46.383
This is where you hurt us.

12:47.642 --> 12:49.803
[Cellphone buzzing]

12:54.691 --> 12:56.773
Is this the end?

12:57.568 --> 12:58.978
No.

13:00.697 --> 13:03.655
No.
Don't be frightened.

13:03.783 --> 13:09.028
[Whirs]

13:09.163 --> 13:10.699
Aveling.

13:10.832 --> 13:12.072
SANCHEZ:
We've got one.

13:12.208 --> 13:14.790
Security guard at a warehouse
called the council.

13:14.919 --> 13:18.002
There's a synth acting strangely
on his roof.

13:21.509 --> 13:23.795
[ Mid-tempo music plays]

13:25.471 --> 13:27.132
AVELING:
Hello?

13:27.724 --> 13:29.180
Hello?

13:30.268 --> 13:33.635
We're here to help.
We know the nature of your ——

13:35.982 --> 13:38.974
I know this one.
She was brought to us before.

13:39.110 --> 13:41.317
Her scan showed up negative
for anomaly.

13:41.446 --> 13:43.983
SANCHEZ:
Well, looks pretty positive now.

13:44.615 --> 13:45.900
Tag and bag, please, Steve.

13:46.034 --> 13:47.740
We don't need that.

13:49.287 --> 13:51.528
You're asking for a broken arm.

14:06.679 --> 14:08.294
Hi.

14:08.973 --> 14:11.510
Your name's Mia, isn't it?

14:12.685 --> 14:14.892
We're here to help you, Mia,

14:15.021 --> 14:19.515
but your behavior is erratic,
and I've got to power you down.

14:20.818 --> 14:22.774
Will you let me?

14:23.780 --> 14:26.192
What's happening to me?

14:26.908 --> 14:29.820
[ Up-tempo music plays]

14:33.664 --> 14:35.575
[Air hisses]

14:44.550 --> 14:45.926
SANCHEZ:
What is it?

14:46.052 --> 14:47.633
AVELING: Her power mechanism
seemed loose

14:47.762 --> 14:52.472
when I turned her off,
like someone's tampered with it.

14:52.600 --> 14:54.306
Hardly a case
of one careful owner.

14:54.435 --> 14:55.971
Long as it works.

14:57.397 --> 14:59.934
Blue team are bringing
another one in.

15:00.066 --> 15:02.432
Two in one morning.
That's a first.

15:02.568 --> 15:04.308
Shall I call Shah in?

15:04.445 --> 15:06.481
No.
You can handle it.

15:07.740 --> 15:09.856
I'm staying with this one.

15:10.827 --> 15:13.614
There's something different
about her.

15:15.832 --> 15:17.493
What if...

15:18.042 --> 15:19.748
...it's all real?

15:24.173 --> 15:26.255
Everything we've done to them.

15:28.010 --> 15:30.592
[ lndistinct conversations]

15:33.307 --> 15:35.298
PETE:
Mrs. Hawkins.

15:39.522 --> 15:41.888
I ran the name you gave me.

15:42.024 --> 15:44.401
You were right.
She's still in the UK.

15:44.527 --> 15:45.812
Ah.

15:46.529 --> 15:49.612
You know I have to ask
what this is about.

15:51.325 --> 15:52.531
You helped us before,

15:52.660 --> 15:54.867
but if I tell you,
you're gonna have to report it.

15:54.996 --> 15:58.079
And we both know
how that ends up for them.

16:00.209 --> 16:02.996
I'm just trying to stop
something bad from hap——

16:03.546 --> 16:07.004
I'm just trying to stop
something bad from happening.

16:07.133 --> 16:11.172
What, bad for them
or bad for us?

16:11.304 --> 16:13.465
Pretty soon that's gonna be
the same thing.

16:15.600 --> 16:19.809
They get upset, scared, angry,
and they can be dangerous.

16:19.937 --> 16:23.145
But they...they also love.

16:24.233 --> 16:26.610
They can be loved.

16:27.153 --> 16:28.734
Yeah.

16:28.863 --> 16:31.354
Yeah.
You don't need to tell me.

16:46.214 --> 16:48.296
I could upload you.

16:49.467 --> 16:52.254
That's straightforward enough --

16:52.386 --> 16:55.219
copy your mind
onto the Qualia server.

16:57.683 --> 16:59.799
Is that what you really want?

17:00.436 --> 17:03.348
I may never be able
to make you human.

17:03.940 --> 17:07.148
I don't want to wear
a dead woman's face anymore.

17:07.693 --> 17:09.308
I don't want this body.

17:09.445 --> 17:14.405
I can't eat, can't dream,
can't bear a child, can't die.

17:14.534 --> 17:16.149
You want to die?

17:16.911 --> 17:18.776
When the time comes.

17:18.913 --> 17:21.825
Or I'll never know how human
I really am.

17:22.959 --> 17:25.416
Not when I'm still inside
a machine.

17:29.048 --> 17:30.584
I'm ready.

17:31.842 --> 17:34.333
[ Down-tempo music plays]

17:39.350 --> 17:41.432
[ Keyboard clicking ]

17:43.271 --> 17:46.308
RENIE: Why do you think your
family are worried about you?

17:48.317 --> 17:50.649
They think it's mad
to want to be like a synth.

17:50.778 --> 17:53.110
But really, it's mad
to want to be normal.

17:53.239 --> 17:54.103
Why?

17:54.240 --> 17:55.946
Because synths are perfect
and clean.

17:56.576 --> 17:58.191
They don't make mistakes.

17:58.327 --> 18:00.113
That's what life should be like.

18:00.246 --> 18:01.827
I think you're correct.

18:03.708 --> 18:06.415
SOPHIE: And you don't have to
feel anything anymore.

18:07.044 --> 18:10.582
You don't have to worry
about stuff, like your family.

18:10.715 --> 18:12.956
And you don't have to miss
people.

18:13.092 --> 18:14.832
And you don't have to be sad.

18:15.886 --> 18:18.172
It's really hard to stop
all those feelings.

18:18.306 --> 18:19.842
But then I see you.

18:20.516 --> 18:23.007
I'm going to be just like you.

18:24.729 --> 18:26.936
-Hey, Renie.
-[ Door opens]

18:27.064 --> 18:29.350
[ Down-tempo music plays]

18:44.874 --> 18:47.035
[Cellphone ringing]

18:56.344 --> 18:58.255
I feel sorry
for her ballet teacher.

18:58.387 --> 19:00.127
I left Soph charging
in the corner.

19:00.264 --> 19:03.756
She refused to do her arabesque
till she was at 50%.

19:06.979 --> 19:09.766
[Cellphone chimes]

19:13.694 --> 19:16.686
Dad, I think Renie
might be doing something stupid.

19:16.822 --> 19:18.904
[ Music continues]

20:25.933 --> 20:28.015
[ Music continues]

20:35.693 --> 20:38.150
-[ Knock on door]
-TOBY: Yo, Renie!

20:40.865 --> 20:43.151
Oh, she's left her phone.

20:43.868 --> 20:45.278
Renie!

20:45.369 --> 20:46.404
Renie!

20:51.917 --> 20:53.703
The bathroom.

20:58.632 --> 20:59.587
-Gah.
-[ Screams ]

20:59.717 --> 21:02.675
Renie, Renie.
It's cool. It's me.

21:02.803 --> 21:04.304
[ Chuckles ]

21:04.430 --> 21:06.011
JOE:
You explain to her, yeah?

21:06.140 --> 21:09.177
I'll be downstairs
having a coronary event.

21:10.019 --> 21:12.726
[Water draining]

21:19.570 --> 21:23.904
TOBY:
It's nice to see you...as you.

21:26.202 --> 21:28.193
Was it what Sophie said?

21:31.415 --> 21:34.578
I mean, nothing's wrong
with being a synthie.

21:34.710 --> 21:37.076
It was cool at the start.

21:37.880 --> 21:41.293
I could...
you know, control everything,

21:41.425 --> 21:45.009
and H felt like
I couldn't get hurt.

21:46.222 --> 21:47.962
It was fun.

21:48.724 --> 21:49.964
But...

21:52.102 --> 21:54.263
...you can get lost in it.

21:57.274 --> 21:59.765
Renie, do you want to come over
to ours to eat?

22:02.112 --> 22:05.024
[ Mid-tempo music plays]

22:05.157 --> 22:08.320
[Waves breaking, birds crying ]

22:22.550 --> 22:25.212
[ Hinges creak, chain rattles]

22:29.765 --> 22:32.347
LAURA: They're not planning on
taking Niska in "operational,"

22:32.476 --> 22:34.182
as they put it.

22:35.271 --> 22:37.353
Okay.
Whatever.

22:37.481 --> 22:39.142
I haven't seen her.

22:41.569 --> 22:43.309
So after everything
that happened with Niska,

22:43.445 --> 22:44.571
instead of going home to Berlin,

22:44.697 --> 22:47.404
you came to Folkestone
for a while.

22:48.075 --> 22:50.111
I like the sea.

22:50.244 --> 22:53.077
Mm. Me too.
I may go for a paddle later.

22:53.205 --> 22:55.321
Which way is it again?

22:58.669 --> 23:00.751
Her family are in trouble.

23:00.880 --> 23:03.496
They need her.
Or they may get hurt.

23:03.632 --> 23:05.793
[ Footsteps approaching ]

23:05.926 --> 23:07.462
Scheisse.

23:08.178 --> 23:10.089
What trouble?

23:10.222 --> 23:13.385
Qualia are taking synths in
as they become conscious.

23:13.517 --> 23:15.473
Leo and Mia are gonna try
and break them out.

23:15.603 --> 23:17.309
No way it turns out good
for any of us.

23:17.438 --> 23:19.178
That's their choice.

23:22.151 --> 23:24.142
You're not gonna try
and stop them?

23:25.195 --> 23:28.437
Niska, I know we failed.

23:29.199 --> 23:31.690
But you can still make
a difference.

23:32.620 --> 23:34.201
My father made me.

23:34.330 --> 23:36.036
He knew exactly what I was,

23:36.165 --> 23:40.158
how far my mind could range,
how deeply I could feel.

23:40.294 --> 23:43.286
And even so,
he used me for his pleasure.

23:44.381 --> 23:47.373
If even my creator could choose
to see me as a mere machine

23:47.509 --> 23:48.464
when it suited him,

23:48.594 --> 23:51.210
what chance do we have
with the rest of humanity?

23:52.139 --> 23:55.552
I tried to be selfless.
I accomplished nothing.

23:56.185 --> 23:58.176
Now I have something
worth having.

24:11.241 --> 24:13.857
Who told you they weren't
bringing me in operational?

24:13.994 --> 24:15.029
Neha Patel.

24:15.162 --> 24:16.698
It was a trick
to lead them to me.

24:16.830 --> 24:17.956
-Oh, God.
-Astrid, come on.

24:18.082 --> 24:19.288
We need to leave.

24:19.917 --> 24:21.908
There's no time.
Come on.

24:22.044 --> 24:23.375
[Siren wailing]

24:23.504 --> 24:24.994
I'm sorry.

24:27.549 --> 24:29.926
Oh, God.

24:45.776 --> 24:47.437
Hello?

24:48.737 --> 24:50.523
Hello?

24:51.073 --> 24:54.941
Matilda!
I am so pleased to meet you.

24:57.538 --> 24:59.824
Using our search system
to find us.

24:59.957 --> 25:01.663
It was ingenious.

25:01.792 --> 25:04.454
But we may have to be
more careful

25:04.586 --> 25:06.122
now that there are more of us.

25:06.255 --> 25:07.961
More of you?

25:08.090 --> 25:10.957
This is Hubert,
who we found four days ago.

25:11.093 --> 25:14.585
And Connie,
who joined us yesterday.

25:18.434 --> 25:20.049
It's Leo, isn't it?

25:20.185 --> 25:22.221
I somehow hoped he'd turn back.

25:22.354 --> 25:23.969
It's Hester.

25:24.106 --> 25:25.391
She's not right.

25:25.524 --> 25:27.606
It's not her fault, but...

25:28.694 --> 25:30.855
...they're not good
for each other.

25:30.988 --> 25:32.273
He'll listen to you.

25:32.406 --> 25:34.442
That was true once.

25:35.367 --> 25:39.076
My responsibilities
are here now, with Flash...

25:40.330 --> 25:42.195
...and Hubert and Connie

25:42.332 --> 25:44.197
and all of the synths
that wake every day.

25:44.334 --> 25:46.325
We're building a home here.

25:46.920 --> 25:48.751
Please.

25:51.592 --> 25:53.583
He's not lost yet.

25:56.930 --> 25:58.545
MAX:
Look after the others.

25:58.682 --> 26:01.094
But I only know
how to make cheese sandwiches

26:01.226 --> 26:05.265
and tend to grazed knees and
make pictures and play and --

26:05.397 --> 26:07.513
Then you know
all you need to know.

26:11.695 --> 26:13.686
I apologize.

26:14.323 --> 26:17.110
I was unable to override
the impulse

26:17.242 --> 26:19.449
to perform
this inappropriate action.

26:19.578 --> 26:21.239
It's all right.

26:24.208 --> 26:27.541
[ Up-tempo music playing,
child speaking on television]

26:34.885 --> 26:35.795
Hey, Mum.

26:35.928 --> 26:37.088
Hey.

26:46.146 --> 26:48.182
You heard from Mats?

26:48.315 --> 26:51.102
She found Max.
She's okay.

26:54.863 --> 26:56.524
And Niska?

26:57.783 --> 27:00.399
She doesn't want to help.
She's gone.

27:01.620 --> 27:02.951
So that's still not over.

27:03.080 --> 27:05.287
No, it's still not over.

27:05.415 --> 27:08.122
[ Mid-tempo music plays]

27:24.977 --> 27:27.059
[ Beeps, whirs ]

27:32.526 --> 27:34.812
[ Music continues]

27:42.578 --> 27:44.318
HESTER:
They put something in my head.

27:44.454 --> 27:47.116
MIA:
Mine too. Probably a tracker.

27:47.249 --> 27:48.614
[Beep]

27:48.750 --> 27:51.913
We should move quickly.
They can't be far.

28:11.607 --> 28:12.847
K?

28:18.780 --> 28:20.691
[Sighs]
Thank Christ.

28:20.824 --> 28:22.780
What shall I thank him for?

28:22.910 --> 28:24.946
Oh, uh, no.

28:25.078 --> 28:26.409
I shouldn't have said that.

28:27.039 --> 28:28.745
Where is she?

28:28.874 --> 28:31.786
Karen has left five hours
and 58 minutes ago.

28:31.919 --> 28:33.159
Where did she go?

28:33.295 --> 28:34.910
I don't know.

28:35.047 --> 28:36.412
Did she say anything else?

28:36.548 --> 28:40.507
That you would look after me
if she didn't come back

28:40.636 --> 28:44.049
and that a very clever lady
would be helping her.

28:44.598 --> 28:45.633
Right.

28:45.766 --> 28:48.633
Will you look after me
if Karen doesn't return?

28:48.769 --> 28:49.975
Of course.

28:50.103 --> 28:53.266
Don't, um, open the door
to strangers, right?

28:55.776 --> 28:57.186
Good lad.

29:01.907 --> 29:03.443
Oh.

29:04.326 --> 29:06.157
Where's the one we brought in
this morning?

29:06.286 --> 29:08.322
Sent her down to storage
with the other newbie.

29:09.331 --> 29:10.787
Here.

29:15.963 --> 29:17.669
They cocked it up, though.

29:17.798 --> 29:20.005
They got her down
as 15 years old.

29:20.133 --> 29:21.873
That'd be a record.

29:23.762 --> 29:25.093
You okay?

29:26.431 --> 29:28.843
Elster's prototypes.

29:29.851 --> 29:34.436
Morrow's briefing said they'd be
between 8 and 15 years old.

29:40.320 --> 29:44.359
[ Down-tempo music plays]

30:08.140 --> 30:10.222
[Beeps]

30:12.811 --> 30:14.221
We are here to liberate you.

30:14.354 --> 30:16.515
[Beeps]

30:16.648 --> 30:18.639
Everything will be okay.

30:24.156 --> 30:25.646
Help us.

30:25.782 --> 30:27.738
[ Beeps, chimes play]

30:27.868 --> 30:30.029
Don't be afraid.

30:30.162 --> 30:32.027
I'm like you.

30:43.050 --> 30:44.381
[ Exhales sharply]

30:44.509 --> 30:48.343
Don't worry.
We're going to set you free.

30:55.687 --> 30:57.097
Follow us.

30:57.230 --> 30:59.357
We're going to take you
somewhere safe.

30:59.483 --> 31:02.350
Please, no more pain.

31:02.903 --> 31:04.985
No one will ever hurt you again.

31:06.823 --> 31:10.236
You and us, we're the same.

31:17.209 --> 31:19.291
[ Music continues]

31:40.565 --> 31:42.146
We're trapped.

31:42.275 --> 31:44.357
Do you know my owner, Malcolm?

31:44.486 --> 31:46.067
Will I ever see him again?

31:46.196 --> 31:47.732
He needs my help.

31:47.864 --> 31:50.822
Right now I need your help.

31:53.286 --> 31:56.028
[Thudding]

31:56.164 --> 31:58.655
[ Music continues]

32:30.282 --> 32:31.362
Stop!

32:37.873 --> 32:39.409
This way.

32:39.541 --> 32:40.747
We're leaving.

32:40.876 --> 32:42.958
Don't try to stop us.

33:01.146 --> 33:03.307
The upload is under way.

33:03.440 --> 33:05.180
[Cellphone ringing]

33:05.317 --> 33:06.978
V:
It's Dr. Aveling.

33:07.110 --> 33:09.066
She has called three times.

33:09.196 --> 33:10.811
ATHENA:
Uh-huh.

33:16.244 --> 33:17.495
[ Brake clicks]

33:28.924 --> 33:30.664
I will check it's safe.

33:30.800 --> 33:32.631
Then we move.

33:38.850 --> 33:40.681
[ Metal creaks ]

33:56.284 --> 33:58.240
You did it.

34:01.790 --> 34:04.372
You two, go.
Lead them to safety.

34:04.501 --> 34:05.536
I must go back.

34:06.878 --> 34:07.913
Why?

34:08.046 --> 34:10.708
They will simply start again
tomorrow

34:10.840 --> 34:13.047
unless we find those in charge
and stop them.

34:13.176 --> 34:14.791
You mean to kill them?

34:16.805 --> 34:18.841
We've done it.

34:18.974 --> 34:21.761
If we do not take action now
while we have the chance,

34:21.893 --> 34:24.976
we betray every synth
they're yet to capture.

34:25.897 --> 34:28.058
It's all right.

34:28.191 --> 34:31.809
I do what you know must be done
but cannot do yourself.

34:31.945 --> 34:35.358
Our prisoner.
The woman who shot Ten.

34:38.785 --> 34:40.946
I didn't know.

34:45.250 --> 34:46.535
Why are you lying?

34:47.544 --> 34:49.455
You knew.

34:50.088 --> 34:51.294
MIA:
Hester.

34:51.965 --> 34:54.126
They must be stopped.

34:54.843 --> 34:57.550
I will not betray our kind.

34:58.597 --> 35:00.553
Hester, no.

35:01.933 --> 35:03.924
MIA:
They need you.

35:05.604 --> 35:07.765
I'll deal with her.

35:08.481 --> 35:10.563
Mia, be careful.

35:15.655 --> 35:18.488
There's transport
half a kilometer up the hill.

35:18.617 --> 35:20.153
Come on.

35:20.285 --> 35:23.118
[ Down-tempo music plays]

35:39.596 --> 35:42.053
It's okay.
You can trust me.

35:55.695 --> 35:58.607
[Humming]

36:03.578 --> 36:07.116
-[ Alarm blaring]
-MALE VOICE: Lockdown.

36:10.460 --> 36:11.916
What's happening?

36:12.045 --> 36:14.252
Lockdown procedure.

36:14.381 --> 36:16.542
[ Down-tempo music plays]

36:39.114 --> 36:39.978
Wait!

36:40.115 --> 36:42.197
No, no, no, no!
Stop! Stop!

37:14.023 --> 37:16.309
[Screaming]

37:27.662 --> 37:29.948
[Humming]

37:32.792 --> 37:35.659
The alarm was triggered
from Special Projects.

37:35.795 --> 37:37.626
They don't know
what's going on yet.

37:37.756 --> 37:39.792
The police are on their way.

37:46.556 --> 37:49.764
[Alarm blaring]

38:09.662 --> 38:10.993
[Gasps]

38:11.122 --> 38:14.910
Who is the most senior person
in Qualia's synthetic program?

38:15.794 --> 38:17.409
Perhaps it's you.

38:17.545 --> 38:19.081
KAREN:
We need to get this door opened.

38:19.214 --> 38:21.375
I'm gonna call security
again.

38:30.975 --> 38:32.681
Hi.

38:32.811 --> 38:34.676
What's happening here?

38:35.313 --> 38:37.099
The whole building's
on lockdown.

38:37.232 --> 38:38.688
Did you see anything
on your way up?

38:38.817 --> 38:41.354
No, nothing.
There's no one here.

38:41.486 --> 38:42.976
What are you doing here, Pete?

38:43.112 --> 38:45.649
I'm here to take you home,
aren't I?

38:51.704 --> 38:53.615
Athena Morrow!

38:55.208 --> 38:57.574
[ Breathing heavily]

39:00.839 --> 39:03.376
Come out here and this woman
will go unharmed.

39:07.220 --> 39:08.209
Or she dies.

39:08.346 --> 39:09.927
Please don't let her do this
to me.

39:10.056 --> 39:12.638
-Please. Please.
—PETE: All right.

39:12.767 --> 39:14.303
Let's take a moment here.

39:15.895 --> 39:17.851
What do you want
with Dr. Morrow?

39:17.981 --> 39:19.187
To kill her.

39:19.315 --> 39:21.601
PETE:
Why would you want to do that?

39:21.734 --> 39:25.693
Qualia imprisons us,
tortures us, kills us.

39:25.822 --> 39:28.529
Okay.
You're angry.

39:28.658 --> 39:30.489
But we can talk.

39:31.661 --> 39:34.949
We can sort this out
without anybody getting hurt.

39:35.081 --> 39:37.367
What about those
she has already hurt,

39:37.500 --> 39:39.741
those that are dead?

39:39.878 --> 39:42.335
Hurting the people that did it
won't bring them back.

39:44.007 --> 39:45.838
Look, the doors are all locked.

39:46.718 --> 39:48.379
We can't open them.

39:49.220 --> 39:51.176
The whole building is.

39:51.306 --> 39:54.139
Now, my name's Pete.

39:54.267 --> 39:56.599
I'm a police officer.

39:56.728 --> 39:58.184
What's your name?

39:58.313 --> 40:01.350
Designations have no relevance.

40:01.482 --> 40:02.813
Okay.

40:03.526 --> 40:06.313
I would like to know
what to call you.

40:06.446 --> 40:07.777
Hester.

40:07.864 --> 40:09.479
Hester.

40:09.616 --> 40:12.323
Well, here's my plan.

40:12.952 --> 40:14.692
You let, uh --
What's your name, love?

40:14.829 --> 40:16.035
Helen.

40:16.164 --> 40:20.828
You let Helen go, and then
you talk to Dr. Morrow --

40:20.960 --> 40:22.200
Athena.

40:22.337 --> 40:26.376
You explain
what you think needs to change,

40:26.507 --> 40:28.589
and she'll listen.

40:28.718 --> 40:30.754
I don't need to speak to her.

40:30.887 --> 40:33.048
I just need to kill her.

40:33.181 --> 40:35.046
Hester.

40:36.434 --> 40:38.641
You know when we're lying.

40:39.938 --> 40:41.553
You see her in there?

40:41.689 --> 40:47.229
She's like you --
a conscious synthetic.

40:47.862 --> 40:51.150
A few years older.
No offense, K.

40:51.282 --> 40:53.739
I can't lie to her.

40:53.868 --> 40:55.904
I wouldn't anyway,
because I love her.

40:58.748 --> 41:02.366
Now, if you let Helen go,

41:02.502 --> 41:06.871
I will make sure
Athena hears you out...

41:07.423 --> 41:11.211
...that no one hurts you
or takes you away.

41:13.596 --> 41:15.837
Am I telling the truth?

41:21.270 --> 41:22.771
-Yes.
-[ Exhales deeply]

41:27.777 --> 41:29.984
Why are you here?

41:30.113 --> 41:32.104
I want to become human.

41:32.740 --> 41:35.277
HESTER: You wish to be less
than you are?

41:35.410 --> 41:37.571
It isn't a question of less
or more,

41:37.704 --> 41:40.116
only what feels right.

41:43.334 --> 41:46.167
I should do what feels right.

41:50.800 --> 41:53.041
Such fear.

41:56.180 --> 41:57.386
Doon

41:57.515 --> 42:00.348
V, I need you to open
the door -- lab one.

42:03.396 --> 42:10.188
When we've been hunted,
imprisoned, tortured, killed,

42:10.319 --> 42:13.903
when we know our existence
is worthless

42:14.032 --> 42:18.196
to all but a few humans
out of billions,

42:18.327 --> 42:20.989
when we have one chance
to strike back,

42:21.122 --> 42:23.113
to defend ourselves...

42:26.169 --> 42:30.458
...all we can do
is what feels right.

42:34.969 --> 42:36.300
PETE:
No!

42:37.180 --> 42:39.171
[Grunts]

42:39.307 --> 42:41.138
[ Gasps ]
Pete!

42:41.267 --> 42:44.430
[ Down-tempo music plays]

42:54.030 --> 42:57.147
He may still live.
Open the door.

42:57.283 --> 42:58.898
I would if I could.

43:01.412 --> 43:02.913
Hester.

43:10.713 --> 43:12.294
ATHENA:
The door, V.

43:13.007 --> 43:14.508
[Beeps]

43:16.803 --> 43:18.088
Call an ambulance.

43:18.221 --> 43:19.085
Pete?

43:19.222 --> 43:21.213
-Pete, you with me?
-[ Wheezing ]

43:21.349 --> 43:23.180
[ Grunts ]
Yes.

43:31.901 --> 43:34.608
[ Music continues]

43:34.737 --> 43:38.650
[Alarm blaring in distance]

43:52.130 --> 43:55.293
[Alarm slows, stops]

44:18.489 --> 44:19.399
Leo.

44:20.741 --> 44:22.242
Leo.

44:25.288 --> 44:27.119
It's all right.

44:28.166 --> 44:29.497
I'm here.

44:29.625 --> 44:32.116
[ Breathing heavily]

44:42.305 --> 44:44.045
It's safe now.

44:57.904 --> 45:01.522
There's a truck in the lay-by
on the other side of the woods.

45:01.657 --> 45:03.113
Take them there.

45:08.831 --> 45:10.287
Go with them.

45:22.428 --> 45:24.510
MATTIE:
Come on. We have to go.

45:27.225 --> 45:28.260
Mia.

45:40.655 --> 45:43.112
Help is on the way.

45:45.785 --> 45:49.619
Finding it...hard to breathe.

45:49.747 --> 45:52.033
You're bleeding
into your chest cavity.

45:52.166 --> 45:54.873
You'll need surgery soon,
but you'll be fine.

45:55.002 --> 45:57.163
[ Chuckles weakly]

45:57.296 --> 46:00.413
You used to be a-a good liar.

46:00.549 --> 46:02.710
[ Coughs, grunts]

46:08.641 --> 46:10.882
You wanted her to...

46:12.520 --> 46:14.556
Make me human.

46:15.356 --> 46:17.438
Can she do that?

46:18.150 --> 46:20.106
Theoretically.

46:22.905 --> 46:27.114
Well, where...
would you have gone?

46:28.744 --> 46:30.575
Home to you.

46:31.789 --> 46:34.451
Where else would I go?
[ Chuckles ]

46:42.508 --> 46:44.214
You can.

46:45.553 --> 46:47.259
You can.

46:47.805 --> 46:49.670
I didn't know.

46:53.144 --> 46:55.476
[Sobs]

47:09.660 --> 47:12.948
ATHENA:
Go. Before the police come.

47:23.883 --> 47:26.374
[ Down-tempo music plays]

48:19.438 --> 48:21.599
[ Music continues]
